videos.description: Sarah Fuller receives a standing ovation as she kicks off and becomes the first woman to play in a Power 5 conference college football game.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Sarah Fuller makes history as she kicks off for Vanderbilt) 2020/11/28 ESHEET

videos.headline: Sarah Fuller makes history as she kicks off for Vanderbilt

videos.description: Missouri head coach Eliah Drinkwitz says the defense brought the momentum by forcing fourth downs and a turnover early in the game.
videos.headline: Missouri defense sets the pace vs. Vandy

videos.description: Missouri started and finished strong on its way to a 41-0 win over Vanderbilt led by Larry Rountree III and his 160 yards and 3 TDs.
videos.headline: Missouri routs Vandy behind Rountree's 3 TDs

videos.description: Soccer star Sarah Fuller and the college sports community reflect on the moment that she became the first woman to compete in Power 5 football.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Sarah Fuller: Her story is history

videos.description: Missouri's Eliah Drinkwitz, a father to four daughters, has an incredible reaction to Sarah Fuller's game that changed history.
videos.headline: Drinkwitz shares amazing perspective on Vandy's Fuller
